content: This app is excellent and does exactly what the description promises. As a root user I am able to enjoy services I pay for (and am entitled to) that might otherwise be unavailable due to my geographical location. One question: I can't seem to get a GPS lock (not WiFi/network) after I disable this app. Is there a trick to restoring actual GPS location? Regardless - I've tried them all, and can honestly say this is the only one that really works. A+ !!
replyContent: Thank you for the review. Yes, you should try rebooting the device. Usually after you stop the service via the stop button it should be ok, but on some devices a reboot is needed, but make sure the app is not enabled to start on boot. Re-enabling the Location services helps as well.
